GDPR Article 30 - Records of processing activities

1. Each controller shall maintain a record of processing activities containing:
(a) the name and contact details of the controller;
(b) the purposes of the processing;
(c) a description of the categories of data subjects and personal data;
(d) the categories of recipients to whom the personal data have been disclosed;
(e) where applicable, transfers of personal data to third countries;
(f) the envisaged time limits for erasure;
(g) a general description of security measures.

GDPR Article 33 - Notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority

1. In the case of a personal data breach, the controller shall without undue delay and, where feasible, not later than 72 hours after having become aware of it, notify the breach to the supervisory authority.

The notification shall at least:
(a) describe the nature of the breach including categories and approximate number of data subjects concerned;
(b) communicate the name and contact details of the DPO;
(c) describe the likely consequences of the breach;
(d) describe the measures taken or proposed to address the breach.

